  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The so-called T -odd correlations in leptonic decays of hadrons due to electromagnetic final state interaction have been calculated. Analysis of these correlations is of interest since they form a masking background for the effects due to possible CP -violation. An accurate measurement of T -odd correlations in K μ 3 0 -decays would in principle allow to determine the electrical radius of the π -meson and in Ξ − → Λ e ν - decays the magnetic moment of the ΣΛ -transition. However, to get this information the existing statistics of the decays should be increased by four orders of magnitude in the first case and by eight orders in the second case.</subfield>
